                                <comments>
                            <comment id="17414740" author="iwasakims" created="Tue, 14 Sep 2021 05:58:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The procedure is described in &lt;a href=&quot;https://cwiki.apache.org/confluence/display/HADOOP2/HowToRelease#HowToRelease-Publishing&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;HowToRelease wiki&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;5. Update upstream branches to make them aware of this new release:&lt;br/&gt;
   a. Copy and commit the CHANGES.md and RELEASENOTES.md:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For example of 2.10.1, I did this to branch-2.10 but missed trunk.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17414741" author="iwasakims" created="Tue, 14 Sep 2021 06:03:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;CHANGES was renamed to CHANGELOG by &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HADOOP-14671&quot; title=&quot;Upgrade to Apache Yetus 0.8.0&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HADOOP-14671&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HADOOP-14671&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17414747" author="iwasakims" created="Tue, 14 Sep 2021 06:14:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;There are some files left as CHANGES instead of CHANGELOG.&lt;/p&gt;

{format}&lt;br/&gt;
$ find . -name &apos;CHANGES*&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
./hadoop-common-project/hadoop-common/src/site/markdown/release/2.10.0/CHANGES.2.10.0.md&lt;br/&gt;
./hadoop-common-project/hadoop-common/src/site/markdown/release/3.1.2/CHANGES.3.1.2.md&lt;br/&gt;
./hadoop-common-project/hadoop-common/src/site/markdown/release/3.1.3/CHANGES.3.1.3.md{format}

&lt;p&gt;While HTML files under &quot;Changelog and Release Notes&quot; pages (hadoop-project/hadoop-project-dist/hadoop-common/release/*) are generated regardless of the file name by &lt;tt&gt;mvn site&lt;/tt&gt;, I would like to rename those to CHNAGELOG here for consistency.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
